  "text": "On the contrary, shear wave elastography developments by Kazemirad et al. may provide promising techniques in quantitative viscoelastic characterization. Loss modulus (i.e. viscosity) and storage modulus (i.e. elasticity), are calculated through this method, which indirectly provides estimation of mechanical properties of soft biological tissues for characterizations in medical applications [CITATION_1] . Unfortunately, the current proposed model is frequency-dependent and is in terms of propagation distance when analyzing the cylindrical shear wave field produced by the homogeneous tissue. This further demonstrates that a more thorough methodology is still needed to provide valid and accurate mechanical characterization of tissue.",
